From: Jiri Slaby <jslaby@suse.cz>
Subject: Revert "PCI: ignore pre-1.1 ASPM quirking when ASPM is disabled"
Patch-mainline: never

This reverts commit 9217bfbbade56ef9dfee88773c2105e619028fa1, upstream
4949be16822e92a18ea0cc1616319926628092ee.

It causes crashes in the early boot:
https://lkml.org/lkml/2012/3/19/227

Signed-off-by: Jiri Slaby <jslaby@suse.cz>
---
 drivers/pci/pcie/aspm.c |    3 ---
 1 file changed, 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/pci/pcie/aspm.c b/drivers/pci/pcie/aspm.c
index 56a6966..e25af67 100644
--- a/drivers/pci/pcie/aspm.c
+++ b/drivers/pci/pcie/aspm.c
@@ -500,9 +500,6 @@ static int pcie_aspm_sanity_check(struct pci_dev *pdev)
 	int pos;
 	u32 reg32;
 
-	if (aspm_disabled)
-		return 0;
-
 	/*
 	 * Some functions in a slot might not all be PCIe functions,
 	 * very strange. Disable ASPM for the whole slot
